	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Bethamia&#44; Forsyth Co. No. Ca.</placeName> <date>May 25th 1860</date>.</p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>Philadelphia&#44; Pa.</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir.</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">My absence from home &#38;<lb/> the pressure of business awaiting me on my return have caused the delay<lb/> of my present answer &#38; remittance&#44; for which I beg your pardon.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Enclosed please find a ten Dollar Bill of the People&#39;s<lb/> Bank <placeName>Charleston&#44; So. Ca.</placeName>&#44; which is amount due you for your<lb/> Bible translation&#44; Catechism &#38; <persName>Dias&#39;</persName> letters all duly received in one<lb/> package through <persName>Adam&#39;s &#38; Co&#39;s</persName> Express.  Although I intended<lb/> to get your Bible&#45;translation after having effected my projected<lb/> &#38; early removal from here.  I am glad that you have anticipated<lb/> my wish by sending the same at the time you did.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I have not had as yet spare time to give the books the necessary<lb/> attention&#44; but hope to be enabled to do it soon.  From a superficial<lb/> perusal of some portions of the same I have been greatly benefitted &#38;<lb/> gratified &#38; I have already gained invaluable instruction.  I en<lb/>tertain the pleasing hope to find there a satisfactory amount of<lb/> affirmative striking &#38; national explanations &#38; the true <hi rend="underline">references</hi> of<lb/> the 53th Chapter &#38; of the 121th verse of the 7th Chap. of <persName>Isaiah</persName><lb/> as well as of the 6 verse of the 12 Chapt. of<persName> Zechariah</persName> <add>&#63;</add><lb/> There is not the most remote doubt in my mind as to the wrong<lb/> &#38; <sic>permited</sic> application <add>&#38; reference</add> of them &#38; similar prophecies&#44; which<lb/> christian commentators give to them&#44; for the whole system of <add>the</add> christian</p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
				<p>religion is hand upon contradictions&#44; nonsense &#38; sacrilegious doctrines</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">But still I would wish to see a more affirmative or<lb/> a more rational &#38; comprehensive explanation on the true<lb/> reference of the above named &#38; similar prophecies</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I will however not precipitate my opinion &#38; <sic>judgement</sic><lb/> on matters of such high importance but endeavour to enlighten<lb/> &#38; instruct myself by attentive perusal &#38; study of the commentaries<lb/> which you have kindly placed into my hands.</p>
				<p>The Kol<add>&#63;</add> <add>Hebrew</add> which you have kindly sent me&#44; shall be thankfully<lb/> returned by first <add>&#63;</add> opportunity.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I ask your pardon for troubling with so long an epistle<lb/> &#38; for <add>&#63;</add> you with such bad English.  I do not pre<lb/>sume any sort of ability in this branch &#38; have but very little<lb/> time just now to bestow upon letter writing.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Please acknowledge Receipt of the enclosed &#38; receipt the<lb/> assurance of my high esteem &#38; deference.</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)"><persName role="author">L. H. Levingston</persName>.</p>
				<p>P. S. You will please to send me No 2. <add>of <date>April</date></add> of the Occident&#44;<lb/> which I have never received.  I would be glad<lb/> to have this as without it some matters in the follo<lb/>wing numbers <del>would</del> could not be understood.</p>
		</body>
